{
  "texts": [
    "However, a systematic and well-established methodology for assessing the condensed graph quality is notably absent in the field [29].",
    "This gap is particularly critical given the complex optimization involved in GC.",
    "The assessment of the condensed graph quality is essential not only for monitoring the condensation progress but also for potentially streamlining the optimization through early-stop strategies.",
    "Currently, GC practices leverage the downstream models, i.e., GNN [26] or graph neural tangent kernel [29], as the indicator for assessment.",
    "However, this method adds considerable computational overhead to the GC process."
  ]
}